      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">The Gardeners' Chronicle Office, ¶ 41, Wellington Street, Strand, W.C. ¶ Telegrams ¶ "Gardchron," London. ¶  ¶ London ¶  March 8,  ¶ 18 ¶ 88....</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">M88.03.08</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Maxwell Masters to Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, MR 130, Miscellaneous <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Reports. <seg style="">Melbourne, Mueller, volume I, p.181.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The spine of this volume has been mistitled as “’Misc Reports Colonial Fruit 1886-97.’ </p>
               </note>The Gardeners' Chronicle Office,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; font-style: italic; "
               xml:lang="en">41, Wellington Street, Strand, W.C.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; font-style: italic; "
               xml:lang="en">Telegrams</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">"Gardchron," London.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">London</seg> March 8, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">18</seg>88.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Private</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir Joseph</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Can</hi>
               </seg> anything be done for Ferd. V. Mueller and the Royal Medal? He is <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>burning with desire to get it and writes <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to me frequently about it <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>always Confidentially and sometimes with adjurations as to secrecy as <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>fervent as those which Shakespeare used with reference to his bones but I find it is no secret and that he has written to Sir Henry Barkly, <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Sclater<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to P. Sclater, December 1887 (in this edition as 87-12-00). </p>
               </note> &amp; others presumably in the same terms — and hence I feel no <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>longer any compunction in writing to you to ask you opinion — I have <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>told him that I am not on the Council and have no influence at all in <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>such matters, but that does not prevent him from writing about it <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>almost by every mail</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>He has certainly deserved well not only on botanical but on <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>geographical grounds but it is not for me to weigh his merits. It <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>would relieve me a little bit if you had time and inclination to tell me in <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">confidence</hi>
               </seg> what you think, but do not trouble to reply to this if in any way inconvenient. I shall understand<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Annotated in pencil by J. Hooker</seg>: wrote 10.3.88.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M was awarded a Royal Medal in 1888, ‘Adjudication of the medals of the Royal Society for the year 1888’, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London. B</seg>, 179, (1888), p. xiii.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">faithfully yrs</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Maxwell T. Masters</p>
         </div>
